definition.value: An organofluorine compound formed by substitution of all the methyl protons in propan-2-ol by fluorine. It is a metabolite of inhalation anesthetic sevoflurane.

A dipeptide that consists of two piperidine-4-carboxylic acid units (connected via amide linkages) where the amino terminus is acylated by a 3-[2-(2-{[4-(indol-3-yl)butanoyl]amino}ethoxy)ethoxy]propanoyl group and the carboxy terminus is formally condensed with the amino group of 3-[2-(2-aminoethoxy)ethoxy]propanoic acid, the carboxy group of which is in turn formally condensed with the alpha-amino group of N(6)-5-nitrofuroyllysine.

A tetrapeptide that consists of four piperidine-4-carboxylic acid units (connected via amide linkages) where the amino terminus is acylated by a 3-[2-(2-{[4-(indol-3-yl)butanoyl]amino}ethoxy)ethoxy]propanoyl group and the carboxy terminus is formally condensed with the amino group of 3-[2-(2-aminoethoxy)ethoxy]propanoic acid, the carboxy group of which is in turn formally condensed with the alpha-amino group of N(6)-5-nitrofuroyllysine bearing a polyether moiety at its carboxy terminus.
An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the non-formylated amino group of arformoterol.
A fumarate salt prepared from arformoterol by reaction of one molecule of fumaric acid for every two molecules of arformoterol.
A fumarate salt prepared from (S,S)-formoterol by reaction of one molecule of fumaric acid for every two molecules of (S,S)-formoterol.
An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the non-formylated amino group of (S,S)-formoterol.
A racemate consisting of equal amounts of arformoterol(1+) and (S,S)-formoterol(1+).
The hydrochloride salt of 2-amino-2-[2-(4-octylphenyl) ethyl]-1,3-propanediol (fingolimod).
An organic cation that is the conjugate acid of fingolimod.
An agonist that binds to and activates sphingosine 1-phosphate receptors.

An aminodiol that consists of propane-1,3-diol having amino and 2-(4-octylphenyl)ethyl substituents at the 2-position. It is a sphingosine 1-phosphate receptor modulator used for the treatment of relapsing-remitting multiple sclerosis. A prodrug, fingolimod is phosphorylated by sphingosine kinase to active metabolite fingolimod-phosphate, a structural analogue of sphingosine 1-phosphate.
An amino trisaccharide consisting of two D-galactose residues, linked alpha(1->3), and an N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residue, linked beta(1->3), at the reducing end.
A three-membered deoxy oligosaccharide which has a 2-acetamido-2,3-dideoxy-D-ribo-hexose unit at the reducing end with an alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl group attached at the 4-position.
A three-membered deoxy oligosaccharide which has a 6-deoxy-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine unit at the reducing end with an alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl group attached at the 4-position.
An N-acyl-beta-D-glucosamine where the N-acyl group is specified as 6-[(2-carboxy-4,6-dinitrophenyl)amino]hexanoyl.
The pyranose form of an N-acyl-D-glucosamine.
An N-acyl-D-glucosamine that has beta-configuration at the anomeric centre.

A dipeptide that consists of beta-alanyl-L-glutamine amide bearing a 2-carboxy-4,6-dinitrophenyl (DNCP) substituent at the amino terminus while the amides at the carboxy terminus and side-chain are substituted by beta-D-glucopyranos-2-yl groups.
An N-substituted diamine that consists of 1,6-hexanediamine bearing two 2-carboxy-4,6-dinitrophenyl (DNCP) substituents at the N(1)- and N(6)-positions.
An organyl group consisting of a benzene ring bearing two nitro substituents at positions 4 and 6 as well as a carboxy group at position 6 relative to the point of attachment.
The organic sodium salt of ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid (EDTA) in which three sodium cations are associated with one trianion of EDTA.

A glycopeptide that consists of glycyl, phenylalanyl, (5R)-5-(beta-D-galactopyranosyloxy)lysyl, glycyl. alpha-glutamyl, glutaminyl, glycyl, prolyl, lysyl, glycyl, alpha-glutamyl and threonine residues coupled in sequence with an isostere-modified IlePsi[(E)-CH=CH]Ala group attached to the amino terminus.

A glycopeptide that consists of glycyl, phenylalanyl, (5R)-5-(beta-D-galactopyranosyloxy)lysyl, glycyl. alpha-glutamyl, glutaminyl, glycyl, prolyl, lysyl, glycyl, alpha-glutamyl and threonine residues coupled in sequence with an isostere-modified IlePsi(CH2CH2)Ala group attached to the amino terminus.

A glycopeptide that consists of phenylalanyl, (5R)-5-(beta-D-galactopyranosyloxy)lysyl, glycyl. alpha-glutamyl, glutaminyl, glycyl, prolyl, lysyl, glycyl, alpha-glutamyl and threonine residues coupled in sequence with an isostere-modified Ile-AlaPsi[(E)-CH=CH]Gly tripeptoid unit attached to the amino terminus.

A glycopeptide that consists of phenylalanyl, (5R)-5-(beta-D-galactopyranosyloxy)lysyl, glycyl. alpha-glutamyl, glutaminyl, glycyl, prolyl, lysyl, glycyl, alpha-glutamyl and threonine residues coupled in sequence with an isostere-modified Ile-AlaPsi(CH2CH2)Gly tripeptoid unit attached to the amino terminus.
A tetracarboxylic acid anion formed by deprotonation of three of the four carboxy groups in ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid (EDTA).

A glycopeptide that consists of (5R)-5-(beta-D-galactopyranosyloxy)lysyl, glycyl. alpha-glutamyl, glutaminyl, glycyl, prolyl, lysyl, glycyl, alpha-glutamyl and threonine residues coupled in sequence with an isostere-modified Ile-Ala-GlyPsi[(E)-CH=CH]Phe tetrapeptoid unit attached to the amino terminus.

A glycopeptide that consists of (5R)-5-(beta-D-galactopyranosyloxy)lysyl, glycyl. alpha-glutamyl, glutaminyl, glycyl, prolyl, lysyl, glycyl, alpha-glutamyl and threonine residues coupled in sequence with an isostere-modified Ile-Ala-GlyPsi(CH2CH2)Phe tetrapeptoid unit attached to the amino terminus.
A pentapeptide that consists of one glycyl, two L-alanyl and two D-alanyl residues coupled in sequence.

An amino tetrasaccharide that consists of 4,6-dideoxy-4-(3-deoxy-L-glycero-tetronamido)-2-Me-alpha-D-Man residue at the non-reducing end coupled to three 4,6-dideoxy-4-(3-deoxy-L-glycero-tetronamido)-2-Me-alpha-D-Man in a linear sequence, connected by (11->2)-linkages.

A polysaccharide derivative that consists of a backbone of alpha-D-glucosyl-(1->4)-5,7-diacetyl-alpha-D-neuraminosyl repeating units, joined together by glycosidic linkages between position 2 of the diacetylneuraminosyl residues and position 6 of the glucosyl residues. The depicted structure is representative and shows the repeating unit, which is variably O-acylated at the 7-position of the neuraminosyl residues.
The amino acid zwitterion formed from 4-hydroxyproline.
A glycal derived from D-galactopyranose
A cyclic enol ether derivative of a sugar having a double bond specifically between carbon atoms 1 and 2 in the ring.
A linear trisaccharide comprising D-glucose (at the reducing end) having a beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-galactosyl moiety at the 4-position.
A galactopentaose in which the linkages between the five D-galactosyl residues are beta(1->3).
A galactopentaose in which the linkages between the five D-galactosyl residues are beta(1->4).
A galactopentaose in which the linkages between the five D-galactosyl residues are beta(1->6).
An O-acyl carbohydrate that consists of alpha-D-galactopyranose bearing five O-acetyl substituents.
Any substance that inhibits the release of insulin
A galactohexaose in which the linkages between the six D-galactosyl residues are beta(1->3).
A galactohexaose in which the linkages between the six D-galactosyl residues are beta(1->4).
A galactohexaose in which the linkages between the six D-galactosyl residues are beta(1->6).
Any rhamnose having D-configuration.
The pyranose ring form of D-rhamnose.
A D-rhamnopyranose having alpha-configuration at its anomeric centre.
An N-acetylmannosamine having D-configuration.
An N-acetyl-D-mannosamine having beta-configuration at its anomeric centre.
An amino disaccharide consisting of beta-D-galactose having an alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl residue attached at the 3-position
